Iavan Pijoos, News24Gautrain. (Duncan Alfreds, News24) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Pretoria - The Gautrain train service between Pretoria and Hatfield has been suspended, the company said on Thursday. Gautrain spokesperson Kesagee Nayager said a Gautrain bus service is currently transporting passengers between these two stations. He said technicians were working to restore the service. The train service to all other Gautrain stations remains unaffected.&nbsp; "We will keep our passengers updated as soon as we have more information on the incident and sincerely apologise for the inconvenience caused." 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.